description: From Ancient Greek σηπτικός (sēptikós, “characterized by putridity”), from σηπτός (sēptós), from σήπειν (sḗpein).

adjectives.description: septic (comparative more septic, superlative most septic)

entries.meaning: Of or pertaining to sewage or the disposal of sewage.
A substance that causes sepsis or putrefaction.
examples: But, in the prosecution of this subject, he had met with very few real septics; and found many substances, commonly accounted such, of a quite opposite nature.

entries.meaning: A septic tank; a system for the disposal of sewage into a septic tank, a septic system.
examples: The question is whether there are any spatial differences in how septics impact water quality, and whether these spatial variations should be considered when regulating septic improvement or removal.

entries.meaning: (mathematics) Of the seventh degree or order.
(mathematics) A mathematical object (function, curve, surface, etc.) of degree seven.
examples: Enriques states that it is possible to construct a family of septics with a singular curve of degree 7 and genus 4 having a triple point that degenerates to the above configuration […] .

description: Short form of Cockney rhyming slang septic tank (“Yank”).

entries.meaning: (UK, Australia, New Zealand, rhyming slang, derogatory) An American, a Yank.
examples: Typical septic. Can't understand why the rest of the world thinks he's a fuck-knuckle.
